<HL>
   Business Brief -- Horizon Industries Inc.:
   Investor Buys More Shares,
   Boosting Interest to 7.58%
</HL>
<DATE>
05/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9B
</SO>
<CO>
   HRZN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Investor M. Edward Ralston said he bought 240,000 shares
of Horizon Industries Inc. common, raising his individual
position in the carpet company to 7.58%.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Mr. Ralston said he bought the 240,000 shares on May 17 for
$7 each.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Ralston is part of a larger shareholder group,
Beaulieu of America Inc., a Dalton, Ga., yarn and carpet
manufacturer, which has said it may seek control of Horizon.
   The additional shares bought by Mr. Ralston bring the
group's combined ownership to about 17.7%.
   Mr. Ralston is president of D&amp;W Carpet &amp; Rug Co., a
Chatsworth, Ga., carpet maker.
   Horizon, based in Calhoun, Ga., declined to comment.
</TEXT>
